    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a large pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the linguine for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the linguine, reserving a cup of <strong>starchy pasta water</strong>, then set it aside until later</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-king-prawn-garlic-and-chilli-linguine-with-spinach/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the linguine is cooking, chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> into quarters</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-king-prawn-garlic-and-chilli-linguine-with-spinach/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim the end[s] from your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> keeping the stalk[s] intact</p><p>Without cutting through the stalk[s], carefully slice the<strong> trimmed courgette[s]</strong> into thin strips, lengthways (at approx. 5mm intervals)</p><p>Then peel the lengths of the<strong> sliced courgette[s] </strong>until you have a pile of 'courgetti'</p><p>Tip: Have a spiraliser? Use this instead!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-king-prawn-garlic-and-chilli-linguine-with-spinach/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped cherry tomatoes</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 6-8 min or until softened and starting to break down</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-king-prawn-garlic-and-chilli-linguine-with-spinach/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Once the tomatoes have softened, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 2-3 min until softened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-king-prawn-garlic-and-chilli-linguine-with-spinach/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Increase the heat to medium-high heat, then drain and add your<strong> king prawns </strong>and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until cooked through</p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-king-prawn-garlic-and-chilli-linguine-with-spinach/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the prawns are cooked, add the <strong>spinach</strong>, <strong>drained linguine </strong>and <strong>courgetti </strong>to the pan and cook until the spinach has wilted</p><p>Remove from the heat and squeeze in the juice of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>then<strong> </strong>give everything a good mix \u2013 this is your <strong>lighter king prawn, garlic & chilli linguine </strong>with<strong> spinach</strong></p><p>Tip: If it's looking a little dry add a splash of the starchy pasta water</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-king-prawn-garlic-and-chilli-linguine-with-spinach/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>lighter king prawn, garlic & chilli linguine with spinach </strong>with a <strong>lemon wedge </strong>to the side</p><p>Finish with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
